fa2png(.c)
- take any .fast(a|q)[.gz] file and convert it to a png 
- For sequences which aren't the same size, give an option to change alignment
  or even allow wrapping (or even stretch each sequence to take the entire row)
- specify width and height in pixels
- provide default colours for DNA/RNA/AA, allow custom colour sets
- give threshold for summarizing function: eg most common base in a block must
  be a greater fraction than 0.5 in order to give the final colour, otherwise
  use the colour for N
- examples to test: the Hug paper alignment; read1 PE150 data from my root
  csRNA-seq; Arabidopsis proteome; a genome?
- maybe go from png back to fa?
